1
00:00:07,450 --> 00:00:11,400
♪ You had a dream inside your head ♪

2
00:00:12,870 --> 00:00:16,400
♪ Wrote the story's end ♪

3
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:20,320
♪ But wrote it in the sand ♪

4
00:00:18,250 --> 00:00:18,730
Corn!

5
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:21,220
What are you two doing?

6
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,010
Nothing.

7
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:25,440
I just got a blister on my foot,

8
00:00:25,590 --> 00:00:27,120
so Jiang Bohan took me home.

9
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:28,760
Your foot?

10
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:30,250
Move aside, move.

11
00:00:31,230 --> 00:00:32,200
Is your foot okay?

12
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,390
It's just a small blister,

13
00:00:33,390 --> 00:00:34,390
nothing serious.

14
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:36,600
I'll put some ointment on it for you later.

15
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:37,060
No need.

16
00:00:38,070 --> 00:00:38,840
Oh, by the way,

17
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,700
why are you just getting back now?

18
00:00:41,070 --> 00:00:41,730
And also...

19
00:00:42,470 --> 00:00:43,800
did you buy these shoes?

20
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:45,410
Where did you get the money?

21
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:48,510
Don't wrongly accuse me.

22
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:49,970
One glance at your shoes

23
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:51,650
and anyone can tell they're expensive.

24
00:00:51,650 --> 00:00:53,450
There's no way I can afford them.

25
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:55,520
Then who bought them?

26
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,060
Jiang Bohan, you bought them, right?

27
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:00,960
Yes.

28
00:01:01,850 --> 00:01:02,210
See?

29
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:06,110
These shoes must be very expensive.

30
00:01:06,110 --> 00:01:07,510
I'll pay you back slowly.

31
00:01:07,740 --> 00:01:08,200
No need.

32
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:09,680
It's a deal, then.

33
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:11,950
I'll go home now.

34
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:13,530
Bye-bye.

35
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:18,170
Bye-bye.

36
00:01:20,430 --> 00:01:20,960
It hurts.

37
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:27,090
Where did you get the money?

38
00:01:28,450 --> 00:01:29,780
Mind your own business.

39
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:45,240
[Close to You]

40
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:47,690
[EP. 21: The World Is a Wreck, But Someone
Always Tries to Mend It]

41
00:02:48,950 --> 00:02:50,880
[Keep Going]

42
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:56,120
Yu Mingxi!

43
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:57,590
Yu Mingxi!

44
00:02:57,590 --> 00:02:58,190
Delivery!

45
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:01,870
Coming.

46
00:03:06,130 --> 00:03:07,330
Still trying to hide?

47
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,000
You're trespassing!

48
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,410
I'm calling the police!

49
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:15,400
Go ahead.

50
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:16,360
Right,

51
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:16,710
come on,

52
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:17,590
call the police.

53
00:03:17,590 --> 00:03:19,240
Even if the police come,

54
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,000
they'll only ask when you're going to pay up.

55
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:21,730
Understand?

56
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,560
How ridiculous.

57
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:27,079
Can't you give me a little more time?

58
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:29,030
I've already paid the principal this month.

59
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:30,030
I just need more time for the interest.

60
00:03:30,030 --> 00:03:31,710
How many extra days have I already given you?

61
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:33,570
You really think we're a charity?

62
00:03:34,740 --> 00:03:36,030
It's written in black and white in the contract—

63
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:36,960
crystal clear.

64
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,490
Your dad signed it himself.

65
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:42,040
But I really don't have any money left.

66
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,210
Let's see. Look.

67
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,160
These shoes are nice.

68
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,240
You can't take these!

69
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,150
Why not?

70
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,190
Are you messing with us?

71
00:03:53,190 --> 00:03:55,079
You have money for shoes, but none to repay us?

72
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,140
It's not like that!

73
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:59,290
These mean a lot to you, right?

74
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,120
Seven days.

75
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:06,160
Bring the money to redeem them.

76
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:07,920
Alright, buddy,

77
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,150
stop wasting your time on her.

78
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:10,150
Seven days later,

79
00:04:10,430 --> 00:04:11,630
if you can't pay up...

80
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:14,160
you'll face the consequences.

81
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:23,950
I'll pay you back,

82
00:04:23,970 --> 00:04:25,570
but you can't take the shoes!

83
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:27,170
Seven days!

84
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:28,040
Pay up!

85
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:31,100
Let's go.

86
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:42,530
Corn!

87
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:44,480
What's wrong?

88
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:45,930
Get up quickly.

89
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:47,810
What happened?

90
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,480
They took the shoes.

91
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:53,650
Shoes?

92
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,480
Let's go back.

93
00:05:04,390 --> 00:05:05,450
What are you doing?

94
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:06,890
Your feet are all dirty,

95
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:07,980
and your leg is scratched.

96
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:09,640
I'll carry you home on my back.

97
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,870
It's just a few steps.

98
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:12,430
Not even if it were just one step!

99
00:05:12,430 --> 00:05:12,830
Get on.

100
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:28,680
Does it hurt?

101
00:05:29,390 --> 00:05:29,720
No.

102
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,050
Still trying to act tough?

103
00:05:32,050 --> 00:05:33,050
It must hurt a lot.

104
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:34,930
Cheer up.

105
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,960
It's just a pair of shoes.

106
00:05:42,940 --> 00:05:44,070
Why is the water off?

107
00:07:02,930 --> 00:07:04,330
Come on, let's continue!

108
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:06,890
What are you doing?

109
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:08,070
Who the hell are you?

110
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,210
He's already in this state, and you're still hitting him?

111
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:11,310
I paid him to be my sparring partner!

112
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:12,440
I can hit him however I want!

113
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,440
Stop, stop, stop.

114
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,360
He signed a contract with us.

115
00:07:15,370 --> 00:07:16,720
Don't meddle in other people's business.

116
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,680
You think money is that easy to earn?

117
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,740
Alright, alright.

118
00:07:19,990 --> 00:07:20,550
I'm fine.

119
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,240
It's none of your business.

120
00:07:20,730 --> 00:07:23,730
♪ It used to be warmer ♪

121
00:07:22,430 --> 00:07:22,920
Come on.

122
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,120
Again.

123
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:25,090
Come on.

124
00:07:25,390 --> 00:07:26,240
Are you crazy?

125
00:07:26,390 --> 00:07:30,260
♪ Saved all the light that was ours ♪

126
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:28,450
I've already told you,

127
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:29,830
it's none of your business!

128
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:31,430
How is it none of my business?

129
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,120
If Yu Mingxi knew how you're making the money,

130
00:07:32,330 --> 00:07:35,670
♪ It's such a long time ♪

131
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,310
don't you think she would be sad?

132
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:35,390
I won't let her know!

133
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:37,650
That depends on whether I tell her or not!

134
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:41,380
♪ Since we retrieved what we are ♪

135
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:42,180
Then what do you want me to do?

136
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:49,180
♪ And all I ask is that you find your smile ♪

137
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:44,850
Are you done yet?

138
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,380
You're chatting away now?

139
00:07:46,510 --> 00:07:48,510
Can we continue the training or not?

140
00:07:53,450 --> 00:08:00,930
♪ And all these thoughts can sit for a while ♪

141
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,440
I'll do it for him.

142
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:51,950
Why did you follow me?

143
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:53,230
Missed me?

144
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:57,910
Haven't had

145
00:08:57,910 --> 00:08:59,110
enough of my punches,

146
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:01,280
and now you want to get beaten by others?

147
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,680
That's called sparring.

148
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:05,620
I'm doing it for money.

149
00:09:10,870 --> 00:09:12,070
How much can you earn?

150
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:15,880
Not a lot from sparring.

151
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:17,630
Just hourly pay.

152
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:20,450
If I'm lucky,

153
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,540
I might win a round.

154
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,530
The bonus is pretty decent.

155
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:24,840
About...

156
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,840
one or two thousand yuan.

157
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,480
So, are you lucky?

158
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,070
Didn't you just see me...

159
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,560
You're playing dumb.

160
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:38,600
You suck,

161
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,270
but your ambitions are big,

162
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:41,870
and you're stubborn as hell.

163
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,950
Who do you take after?

164
00:09:47,630 --> 00:09:48,960
After my dad, of course.

165
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,300
Didn't Corn...

166
00:09:57,550 --> 00:10:00,810
tell you about the relationship
between our two families?

167
00:10:02,830 --> 00:10:03,360
No.

168
00:10:31,390 --> 00:10:32,360
Back then,

169
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:34,960
my dad got involved in some investment scheme.

170
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,550
At first, he enjoyed some early gains

171
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:38,150
and made quite a bit of money.

172
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:40,240
So, he persuaded Yu Mingxi's dad

173
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:41,120
to join in too.

174
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:43,950
They borrowed all the money they could.

175
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:45,270
In the end,

176
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,200
they were both scammed

177
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,400
and lost everything.

178
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,410
My coward of a dad

179
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:54,600
couldn't face reality.

180
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:56,620
He sold the house

181
00:10:56,620 --> 00:10:57,680
to pay off his debts

182
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,410
and then just vanished.

183
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:04,440
After Yu Mingxi's dad passed away unexpectedly,

184
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:07,370
it was just she and her mom—two fools—

185
00:11:07,430 --> 00:11:09,360
working hard to pay back the debts.

186
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,330
What about your mother?

187
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:17,480
My mother?

188
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:22,080
She divorced my father long ago.

189
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:25,470
I was placed in my father's custody.

190
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,940
Later, she remarried and had another child.

191
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,270
I'm the stain in her past

192
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:32,800
that makes her hang her head in her new family.

193
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,680
And I'm not thick-skinned,

194
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:36,030
so eventually...

195
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,840
I stopped bothering her.

196
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:39,810
So...

197
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:43,410
you went to live with Yu Mingxi's family

198
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,000
just to make it up to them?

199
00:11:50,190 --> 00:11:51,320
Make it up to them...

200
00:11:54,930 --> 00:11:56,460
It'd be hard to ever do that.

201
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,140
Besides those two,

202
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:01,360
I've got

203
00:12:02,110 --> 00:12:03,510
no one else in this world.

204
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,620
I also don't know where else to go.

205
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:17,370
You fought in those boxing matches...

206
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:20,120
to help them pay off the debt, right?

207
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,170
I did before,

208
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:26,080
but not anymore.

209
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:31,270
I didn't expect those high heels to be so expensive.

210
00:12:31,270 --> 00:12:33,530
It cost me two months' salary in advance.

211
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,700
No matter what,

212
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,580
she can't know about this.

213
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,200
Don't go out boxing anymore.

214
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,140
As for the money...

215
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:52,840
I'll take care of it.

216
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:55,680
What are you talking about?

217
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,860
What does this have to do with you?

218
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:00,680
Don't take everything upon yourself.

219
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:03,740
How does this have nothing to do with me?

220
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,500
I care about Yu Mingxi.

221
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,450
She cares about you.

222
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:16,260
Consider this as me caring about both of you.

223
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:23,630
You still want your Coke or not?

224
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:24,760
If not, give it to me.

225
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:41,750
You don't need to send me home.

226
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:44,520
Who said I'm sending you home?

227
00:13:46,370 --> 00:13:47,890
I'm here to see Yu Mingxi.

228
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:50,270
Hands off.

229
00:13:51,050 --> 00:13:52,050
No respect at all.

230
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:56,940
Yu Mingxi has always treated you like her own brother.

231
00:13:56,940 --> 00:13:58,910
So shouldn't you call me...

232
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:00,790
"Brother-in-law?"

233
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:04,330
Wait until it's official to say that.

234
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:11,760
-Why did you come out?
-Why did you come out?

235
00:14:11,980 --> 00:14:12,490
I...

236
00:14:19,410 --> 00:14:20,940
Did you two get into a fight?

237
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:23,840
Well...

238
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:26,840
We just...

239
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:28,520
had a little scuffle,

240
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,720
but we've already...

241
00:14:30,370 --> 00:14:30,890
made up.

242
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,010
It hurts!

243
00:14:33,710 --> 00:14:34,590
What's wrong?

244
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:37,450
Where does it hurt?

245
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:39,590
I hurt all over.

246
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:41,910
Everywhere hurts.

247
00:14:41,930 --> 00:14:43,010
Why did you hit him?

248
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:44,230
Come on, let's go home.

249
00:14:44,230 --> 00:14:44,740
Okay.

250
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,610
What's with your clothes?

251
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:10,850
I accidentally spilled Coke on them earlier.

252
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:12,430
Take them off.

253
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:13,300
Why?

254
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:15,030
They're all dirty.

255
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:16,300
It's fine.

256
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:17,720
I'll wash them myself when I have time.

257
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,270
Now!

258
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:20,420
Alright.

259
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:25,020
Doesn't he have hands of his own?

260
00:15:25,020 --> 00:15:27,150
Why do you need to wash his clothes for him?

261
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:28,810
They need to be washed anyway.

262
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:30,210
Might as well save water.

263
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:32,690
Jealous, aren't you?

264
00:15:32,690 --> 00:15:33,910
You Jingchu.

265
00:15:35,290 --> 00:15:36,130
How childish.

266
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:41,840
What happened to your leg?

267
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:44,920
It's nothing.

268
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:47,050
I accidentally fell a few days ago.

269
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,320
How did it happen?

270
00:15:49,630 --> 00:15:51,040
We were messing around a couple of days ago,

271
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:53,570
and she accidentally bumped into something.

272
00:15:59,160 --> 00:15:59,590
Here.

273
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:06,270
You Jingchu!

274
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,700
Why are you all bruised up again?

275
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:11,440
I'm fine.

276
00:16:11,460 --> 00:16:12,120
No big deal.

277
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,640
Why do you always get yourself injured?

278
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,880
It's because

279
00:16:18,910 --> 00:16:19,840
I have thin skin.

280
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,680
I bruise like a peach.

281
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:22,630
It looks worse than it actually is,

282
00:16:22,630 --> 00:16:24,290
but it doesn't hurt that much.

283
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,080
I'm going to do the laundry now.

284
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:26,630
Sit down.

285
00:16:26,890 --> 00:16:27,920
Let me put some ointment on you first.

286
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,120
Give me your clothes.

287
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:55,560
I'm not telling you all this

288
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:57,540
to gain your sympathy...

289
00:16:59,510 --> 00:17:00,440
but to make you

